We went back to Arco, long a family-run local favorite, shortly after indoor dining was allowed again. It was great as always — food, service, atmosphere — and reassuring with all the safety measures in place, including distanced tables.  Can’t beat the fresh pasta, spun out right there in the front window, and the handmade sauces. Try the Brussels sprout salad to go along. NYC is coming back.

Believe me it's not easy to find a place in Manhattan where you can sit down and eat a meal with $ 12 or so, and it's easy to reach by metro, being just a short distance from two stops on two different lines. It is worth moving from anywhere in the city. Recommended  (Original) Un locale carino, silenzioso, con cibo italiano e in particolare sardo ben cucinato, servizio discreto e non invadente, prezzi nella media per NY ma che diventano convenienti in rapporto alla qualità dei piatti serviti. Assolutamente concorrenziale il menu a pranzo dal lunedi al venerdi, rischiate di pagare un pasto piu che dignitoso meno che un panino magari mangiato di fretta dopo aver fatto la fila per ordinarlo. Credetemi non è facile trovare un posto a Manhattan dove potersi sedere e mangiare un pasto con 12 dollari o poco piu', inoltre è facile da raggiungere in metro, trovandosi a poca distanza da due fermate di due linee diverse. (Translated by Google) Restaurant of Italian cuisine and in particular with foods from Sardinia, easily accessible by metro (located between two stops) a stone's throw from Central Park. Quiet environment, attentive service, unobtrusive music, no TV (how nice !!), I absolutely recommend a stop for lunch where you can sit at a clean and quiet table and choose from a varied menu of dishes at a cost of only 13/14 dollars , in my opinion the best value for money for a lunch in the city, excellent homemade pasta. At dinner the menu is less cheap but still largely in line with NY prices, while still maintaining excellent value for money. There is also a good choice of wines, a must for anyone who needs a true Italian meal that is not camouflaged. in conclusion absolutely recommended.  (Original) Ristorante di cucina Italiana ed in particolare con cibi provenienti dalla Sardegna, facilmente raggiungibile in metro (si trova tra due fermate) a due passi da Central Park. Ambiente tranquillo, servizio attento, musica non invadente, niente tv (che bello!!), consiglio assolutamente una sosta a pranzo dove potrete sedervi in un tavolo pulito e tranquillo e scegliere in un variegato menu pietanze con una spesa di soli 13/14 dollari, secondo me il miglior rapporto qualità prezzo per un pranzo in città, ottima pasta fatta in casa. A cena il menu' è meno economico ma comunque ampiamente in linea con i prezzi di NY, mantenendo comunque un ottimo rapporto prezzo qualità. Buona anche la scelta dei vini, immancabile per chi ha bisogno di un pasto all'italiana vero e non camuffato. in conclusione consigliato assolutamente.

I opted for the factory pick-up.  When I got there, I was greeted by Sara herself and she truly could not have been nicer.  We spent quite a bit of time chatting, then she gave me my order and a few complimentary pieces of her biscotti.  When you find a product you like, it's even better when you find that you like the person who makes it.  Whether you're vegan or otherwise, Sweet & Sara makes delicious stuff.

My friends, Robert and Leslie took me to Arco just a few days ago, hoping I would love it.  They were right!  I have been at Arco 3 days running; two dinners and a lunch, once with my two friends, lunch with a fellow photographer (mlle) from Paris and tonight, by mysef.  All these events were a success!  Good, quiet service, friendly and the food was very good. The dinner special on the first night was Special!  Grilled calamari and accompaniments was first rate.  The grilled salmon was as ordered.  For lunch the next day I tried the mussel stew and was not disappointed.  Tonight  I dined alone, had a nice conversation with your representative from Israel.  she guided me to an Italian beer on tap to go with the  grilled baby octopus.  Spicy and delicious.  She happily permitted me to sample a few white wines before I chose the Friuli to go with my order of pasta with clams.  And I liked it so much I requested a doggy bag for later.  A perfect, strong cappucino ended the meal and I left,  a happy (old) puppy! Do not be surprised if you see me there soon, for more Arco goodies! Len
